race.comment: PULL MY FINGER (6) produced a nice effort on debut in better company last start over 1000m at Ballarat when second, beaten 0.8 lengths. Has the inside gate so he will prove tough to beat. FROSTED IN TIME (3) finished third, beaten 1.75 lengths, when resuming from a spell last start over 1000m at Echuca. Nicely placed to go a couple better. BALLISTIC BLUE (1) resumes from a spell of six months. Could only manage to finish fifth at the latest run over 1300m at Cranbourne. Should be forward enough following two recent trials. Can kick off with a bold showing. MADAM BURBERRY (13) could be a sneaky one for the exotics at a price now she's third up and has had the earmuffs applied.
